    • Method Detail

      • process

        protected boolean process(CommandSender sender,
                          String[] label,
                          String argument)
        Process the given argument. This will parse it into it's appropriate form, as well as validate that it is in the proper state. The value returned represents whether or not the process was successful. No error message is required beyond what was already sent within the parsers and validators.
        Parameters:
        sender - the sender of the command.
        label - the label of the command.
        argument - the raw string argument to be processed.
        Returns:
        true if the process was successful. Otherwise, returns false.

      • getRecommendations

        protected List<String> getRecommendations(CommandSender sender,
                                          String lastWord)
        Retrieves all potential options a player can have when trying to tab-complete this argument. This should always be implemented. However, because that most likely will not happen, it defaults to the same behavior that Bukkit uses which is to list off the names of all visible connected players.
        Parameters:
        sender - the sender who is tab-completing.
        lastWord - the last word in the player's tab complete.
        Returns:
        all argument options.

        public boolean hasPermission()
        Returns:
        true if the argument has a required rank. Otherwise returns false.

      • getPermission

        public Permission getPermission()
        The ability to use an argument might differ from the ability to use a command in general. This is the rank required to use this argument within a command.
        Returns:
        the rank required to use this argument.

      • setPermission

        public void setPermission(Permission permission)
        Sets the required permission for this argument. This should only be set once, and should only be changed from the CommandArgumentBuilder. Will throw an IllegalStateException if set a second time.
        Parameters:
        permission - the required permission.

      • getOrdinal

        public int getOrdinal()
        Gets where in the order of arguments this argument falls for a particular command. The default is -1, so if -1 is returned it means that this argument has not yet been assigned to a command.
        Returns:
        the argument ordinal.

      • setOrdinal

        protected void setOrdinal(int ordinal)
        Sets the order that this argument falls for a particular command. This method is protected to make sure that the CommandHandler does not break when managing the argument system.
        Parameters:
        ordinal - the new argument ordinal.
